David Montgomery is with Jennifer Treitmaier-Honaker and Anita Martin Slade.
April 13, 2017 at 12:54 AM ¬∑

Preble County stingrays has started their conditioning for the upcoming summer season at the Preble County YMCA.

Conditioning times for ages 10 and under is 4:30-5:30 p.m., ages 11-18 the time is 5:20 to 6:30 on Monday, Tuesday and Thursday. There will be two different sessions, session one April 10th to May 4th and session two May 8th to June 1st. The cost for one session is $45 or $80 if you sign up for both sessions. If you have more than one child and you sign up for both sessions, the cost for the 2nd child is $40 for one session or $70 for both sessions, and 3 or more the cost is $35 per child and $50 for both sessions. It is not a requirement to do conditioning to be on the Stingrays.

The first outdoor practice is June 5th if you are looking for something for your kids to do this summer. Look forward to seeing everyone out for a good swim.

Blazer Youth Wrestling
December 18, 2016 at 8:05 PM ¬∑

Very good first wrestling meet for us today! Alot of tough competition and we held our own for sure. The hard work being put fourth by the kids definitely was shown.

We had 35 wins and 21 losses as a whole. 9 first place finishes ( awesome considering we only had 19 kids wrestling) , 3 second place finishes, 4 third place finishes, and 3 fourth place finishes.

Proud of all the wrestler's in our club and if they didn't do so well, tell them to keep their heads up, we do pay attention to what they need improvement on and will begin working on it. That being said this week's 1st place finishers are: Jeffrey Ricketts Jr, Mason Cordle, Andrew Hamm, Dylan Smith, Grady Ott, Henry Toschlog, Grayson Reynolds, Zack Creager, and Tyler Hoover!

Thanks to everyone for all your help today. See everyone on Tuesday!

Teresa Glander McPherson‚ÄéNational Trail High School Football
October 6, 2016 at 9:41 PM ¬∑

I would like to challenge all the high school football players and coaches to come out Saturday at Tri-Village to watch the Pee-Wee football players in action. These boys sit in the stands (sometimes driving me crazy) supporting you on Friday nights!! We cannot continue to build high school football team without these kids continuing to play and if we don't support each other then they likely won't. We have to get them excited that the high school coaches and players are watching them and foster that difficult decision from 8th grade to high school whether they will play or not. It might take one of you to make a difference in one of these young boys lives......be that difference!!!!! To the peewee kids and parents Tyler cannot be there Saturday as he has to be at UD for a football visit but tell the boys to win and we will be there Sunday!!

post_text: CONGRATULATIONS BLAZER YFL! GOOD LUCK IN THE POSTSEASON!
shared_text:
Eric Lee is with Cooper Lee and 6 others.
October 2, 2016 at 7:08 PM ¬∑

BLAZER PRIDE!!

The Varsity Blazer Youth Football team finished the regular season undefeated at 6-0!! These boys play with determination, passion, confidence and heart like I've never seen. I can't say enough about the boys and their drive to do their best and get better every day! It shows on the scoreboard!

Once again, we're counting off those points! The Blazers gave the Tri-Village Patriots a good old fashioned 46-20 beat down!

I also want to give a shout out to the JV team who plays with just as much passion and conviction as the Varsity boys. They finished their regular season at 5-1 today against a team that, without going into details, had an unfair advantage. Hold your heads high boys and let's get ready for the play-offs!

We (both JV and Varsity teams) return next Saturday to the Patriots' field again for the first play-off game. Come on out and support these boys as they will be sure to put on a show you won't forget! JV at 2 pm and Varsity at 4 pm.

Santa shop is going on this week.

On Thursday, we will have gift cards in the Commons after the elementary Christmas program, so plan for that. There is an order form in our Photos tab for the cards that we have on hand-- why not plan to do some Christmas shopping? We accept cash and checks.

Saturday is the annual Santa breakfast. Breakfast tickets are on sale all week. The presale order form is also in our Photos tab. Lots of awesome NT entertainment and vendors will be present. Also during the breakfast, Tina Ebright from Jacob's Ladder will speak to us regarding the Jacob's Ladder organization and how we all can help this holiday season.

As always, thank you for liking and sharing our post so that everyone in our network will receive this information!

Everyone have an AWESOME week.

Reminders for December:

PTO is busy, busy in December.

~ Thursday the 4th is our December PTO meeting at 6:30 in the teacher center.

~ Monday the 8th begins Santa's Secret Shop for K-6th grade. It runs through Friday the 12th. Look for the shopping lists to come home.

~ Saturday the 13th is the annual Holiday Breakfast featuring Santa Claus. There is a lot of entertainment that you won't want to miss. Debuting their talents will be the NT Kindergarten Singers. The NT Steel Drums, NTHS Choir and the Wonderettes will also perform. Pre-sale Breakfast tickets are on sale for $3 ($5 at the door) and will be on sale until December 12. Entertainment is free.

Gift cards are also available. The abbreviated order form is list on our page. The complete list can be found at www.shopwithscrip.com

Tomorrow is our first home game! The game begins at 7:30pm vs. Twin Valley South. Come out to support our Blazers.

There has been a very generous, anonymous gift made to NT that was used for new stadium bleachers, scoreboards and also enabled us to refinish the HS gym floor to name a few. Please help us show our gratitude by sending a card of thanks to this donor. A "thank you" card collection box will be set-up at the game.

As you are filling out your childs school forms, please take a moment to look over the PTO volunteer sheet. Please consider getting involved and/or continuing your involvement.
We are only able to do the great things we do because of parent and teacher involvement.

Please share this information with other parents as well. NTPTO primarily serves grades K-6.

Mark your calendar for our first PTO meeting: Thursday, September 4 @ 6:30. Meetings will be the first Thursday of every month @ 6:30.

post_text:
ANNUAL PTO Father/Daughter Dance
Friday, February 21, 2014 7:00pm-9:00pm
Kindergarten through 6th grade girls are invited to attend.
The cost is $5 per couple and $2 for each additional family member. Money will be collected at the door.
Flowers will be sold at the dance for $1 and $2. Pictures will also be taken for a small fee.
Light refreshments will be provided
Questions should be directed to Tonya Allen 533-7583
*all girls must be NT students to attend.
